"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Add `[Y/n/a]` to Commit Prompt & Simplify `commit_linking`\n\n## Context\n\nThe `commit_linking` setting currently has complex setup-time logic: `isFirstSetup` detection, `migrateProjectSettings()`, struct-copy-and-strip to exclude `commit_linking` from `settings.local.json`, and duplicated save blocks. This complexity caused bugs during manual testing (local settings overriding project settings, hook binary mismatches).\n\nThe better UX: let users discover `commit_linking: \"always\"` through the commit prompt itself with `[Y/n/a]`. When they pick `a`, it writes the preference to `settings.local.json`. This is a personal preference, so local settings is the right home. This eliminates all the setup-time complexity.\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n### Step 1: Modify `askConfirmTTY` to support three-way response\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\n\n- Add `ttyConfirmResult` type with `ttyConfirmYes`, `ttyConfirmNo`, `ttyConfirmAlways` constants\n- Change `askConfirmTTY` return type from `bool` to `ttyConfirmResult`\n- Update hint from `[Y/n]` to `[Y/n/a]`\n- Add `\"a\", \"always\"` case returning `ttyConfirmAlways`\n- Update all early returns (test mode, Gemini CLI, TTY failure) to return result type instead of bool\n\n### Step 2: Add `saveCommitLinkingAlways` helper\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\n\nAdd helper that loads existing `settings.local.json` (via `settings.LoadFromFile`), sets `CommitLinking = \"always\"`, and saves back via `settings.SaveLocal(ctx, ...)`. Must load existing file first to preserve other local overrides (especially `Enabled` which is not `omitempty`).\n\n```go\nfunc saveCommitLinkingAlways(ctx context.Context) error {\n    localPath, err := paths.AbsPath(ctx, settings.EntireSettingsLocalFile)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"resolving local settings path: %w\", err)\n    }\n    local, err := settings.LoadFromFile(localPath)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"loading local settings: %w\", err)\n    }\n    local.CommitLinking = settings.CommitLinkingAlways\n    return settings.SaveLocal(ctx, local)\n}\n```\n\n### Step 3: Update `PrepareCommitMsg` call site\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` (lines 359-381)\n\nChange the `source=\"message\"` branch to handle three-way result:\n- `ttyConfirmNo` → return nil (don't link, same as before)\n- `ttyConfirmAlways` → call `saveCommitLinkingAlways(ctx)`, log warning if it fails (non-fatal), then fall through to add trailer\n- `ttyConfirmYes` → fall through to add trailer (same as before)\n\nBoth `ttyConfirmYes` and `ttyConfirmAlways` add the trailer.\n\n### Step 4: Simplify `setup.go`\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/setup.go`\n\n**In `runEnableInteractive`** (lines 156-280):\n- Remove `isFirstSetup` check (line 173)\n- Remove commit_linking initialization block (lines 189-199)\n- Remove `settings.Strategy = \"\"` line (line 199)\n- Replace complex save blocks (lines 222-241 and 260-272) with simple helper:\n\n```go\nsaveSettings := func() error {\n    if shouldUseLocal {\n        return SaveEntireSettingsLocal(ctx, settings)\n    }\n    return SaveEntireSettings(ctx, settings)\n}\n```\n\n**In `setupAgentHooksNonInteractive`** (lines 598-690):\n- Remove `isFirstSetup` check (line 616)\n- Remove commit_linking initialization block (lines 633-641)\n\n**Remove `migrateProjectSettings` function entirely** (lines 726-747).\n\n### Step 5: Clean up `config.go`\n\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/config.go`\n\nRemove `CommitLinkingAlways` and `CommitLinkingPrompt` aliases — they were only used in `setup.go` which no longer needs them.\n\n### Step 6: Run checks and update tests\n\n- `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\n- Existing tests should pass — `GetCommitLinking()` default behavior unchanged, integration tests use `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=1` which returns `ttyConfirmYes`\n\n## What doesn't change\n\n- `settings.go`: `CommitLinking` field, `GetCommitLinking()`, constants, validation in `loadFromFile`/`mergeJSON` — all stay as-is\n- `PrepareCommitMsg`: the `commitLinking == settings.CommitLinkingAlways` auto-link path stays (for users who already have the setting)\n- Editor flow (no `-m` flag): still adds trailer with comment, no prompt\n- Agent fast path (no TTY): still auto-links, no prompt\n- Deprecated `Strategy` field: left alone, `omitempty` handles cleanup on next save\n\n## Migration Behavior\n\n| User type | Behavior |\n|-----------|----------|\n| New user | Sees `[Y/n/a]` on first commit, can pick `a` to auto-link forever |\n| Existing user (no `commit_linking` set) | Same prompt as before, now with `a` option |\n| User who already has `commit_linking: \"always\"` | Auto-links, no prompt (unchanged) |\n| User who picks `a` at prompt | `settings.local.json` gets `commit_linking: \"always\"`, future commits auto-link |\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint` — passes\n2. `mise run test:ci` — all tests pass\n3. Manual testing:\n   - `git commit -m \"test\"` with active session → prompt shows `[Y/n/a]`\n   - Press `a` → commit links, `settings.local.json` now has `commit_linking: \"always\"`\n   - Next `git commit -m \"test\"` → auto-links without prompt\n   - Fresh `entire enable` → no `commit_linking` in settings (clean)\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/evisdrenova/.claude/projects/-Users-evisdrenova-code-entire-devenv-cli/258a514e-cd22-4513-94b6-49095182e3fa.jsonl\n\n---\n\ncommit and push this"